  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA9-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu uṭaṉpōkāniṉṟa talaimakaṉ talaimakaṭku uraittatu. (note G1+2: 1. itu puṇarcci nikaḻntatu. 2. itu puṇarcci makiḻntapiṉ vaḻivanta na... varuntātē ceṉṟatu.)</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what HE, who was eloping [with her], said to HER. </p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA9">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            aḻivilar muyalu mārva mākkaḷ</l>
<l>            vaḻipaṭu teyvaṅ kaṭkaṇ ṭāaṅ</l>
<l>            kalamaral varuttan tīra yāḻaniṉ</l>
<l>            ṉalameṉ paṇaittō ḷeytiṉa mākap</l>
<l>            porippūm puṉki ṉeḻiṟṟakai yoṇmuṟi </l>
<l>            cuṇaṅkaṇi vaṉamulai yaṇaṅkukoḷat timiri</l>
<l>            niḻalkāṇ ṭōṟu neṭiya vaiki</l>
<l>            maṇalkāṇ ṭōṟum vaṇṭa ṟaii</l>
<l>            varuntā tēkumati vāleyiṟ ṟōyē</l>
<l>            mānaṉai koḻuti makiḻkuyi lālu </l>
<l>            naṟuntaṇ poḻila kāṉaṅ</l>
<l>            kuṟumpa lūrayāñ cellu māṟē.</l>

        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l rend="indent2">When, like people, desirous to exert themselves without causing loss,</l>
        <l rend="indent3">upon seeing with [their] eyes the god they had set out for,</l>
        <l>we will have attained your good soft bamboo shoulders,</l>
        <l rend="indent">so that the whirling misery ends,</l>
        <l>– when the torment<note place="foot">Here there is a clear instance of <term xml:lang="ta">aṇaṅku</term> not refering to a (malevolent) spirit nor yet to any mysterious female quality, but simply to the girl's being weary with the long walk in the heat.</note> increases in your beautiful breast adorned</l>
        <l>with beauty spots, [like] the graceful bright sprouts on the Puṉku tree</l>
        <l rend="indent">with flowers [resembling] parched rice,<note place="foot">This line is either an implicit comparison for HER or the specification of the shade mentioned in line 7.</note></l>
        <l>whenever [you] see shade you may stay long,</l>
        <l>whenever [you] see sand you may join it in play,</l>
        <l>you may go without worry, o you of white teeth.</l>
        <l>The way we will go has many small villages</l>
        <l rend="indent">in forests with fragrant cool groves,</l>
        <l rend="indent3">where the joyous Koel dance, picking at big buds<note place="foot">Or <term xml:lang="ta">mā naṉai</term> "mango buds".</note>.</l>
    </lg>
         </div>
